</taxonomicName>
. Although they illustrated a pair of moths and the genitalia of this species, they did not record their localities, because they did not revise this species in their “revision of Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE825BFF3D77DD9FA62" authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1866" box="[990,1160,1467,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE825BFF3D77D7EFA62" box="[990,1071,1467,1491]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Naarda</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
”, but changed the generic combination only (
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82702F3B37B0EFA49" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[355,607,1503,1528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref3670" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2014 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 1. Taxonomic notes and description of 28 new species from Asia. Oriental Insects, 48 (1 - 2), 1 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2014.959790" type="journal article" year="2014">Tóth &amp; Ronkay, 2014a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE8240AF3B37BFEFA46" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[619,687,1503,1527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="9 - 18" refId="ref3743" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2014 b) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 3. Description of three new species from Asia. Nota Lepidopterologica, 37 (1), 9 - 18. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 37.7957" type="journal article" year="2014">
2014 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE824C3F3B37BFEFA46" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[674,687,1503,1527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="3 - 23" refId="ref3813" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2015 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 2. Description of ten new species from Asia. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 61 (1), 3 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.17109 / AZH. 61.1.3.2015" type="journal article" year="2015">b</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 2015a, 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE8256AF3B37A00FA46" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[779,849,1503,1527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="253 - 262" refId="ref3886" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2015 b) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 4. Description of nine new species. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 18 (2), 253 - 262. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2015.02.001" type="journal article" year="2015">
2015 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82522F3B37A00FA46" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[835,849,1503,1527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="179 - 201" refId="ref3956" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2015 c) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 5. Description of 13 new species from Asia. Zootaxa, 3925 (2), 179 - 201. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3925.2.2" type="journal article" year="2015">b</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 2015c). According to Dr. Balázs Tóth (personal communication in 2021), all the illustrated specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE824BCF06F7AFBF9AA" authorityName=": Toth &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2014" box="[733,938,1539,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctirena">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE824BCF06F7AFBF9AA" box="[733,938,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Naarda punctirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
